<title>Developing z/OS applications with Eclipse</title>
<titlealts>
<navtitle>Developing z/OS applications with Eclipse</navtitle>
<searchtitle>Developing z/OS applications with Eclipse</searchtitle>
</titlealts>
<shortdesc>The <keyword
conref="../../com.ibm.wsentdev.doc/topics/prodnames.dita#auroraproducts/RDZ_fam"/> Eclipse
integrated development environment (zIDE) provides tools for developing COBOL, PL/I, Assembler,
REXX, and C++ applications in local and remote systems. These tools include support for JCL
procedures, <tm tmtype="reg" trademark="CICS">CICS</tm> and IMS applications, and <tm tmtype="reg"
trademark="Db2">Db2</tm> programming.</shortdesc>
<prolog>
<metadata>
<keywords>
<indexterm>z/OS Integrated Development Environment</indexterm>
<indexterm>zIDE</indexterm>
<indexterm>z/OS development tools</indexterm>
</keywords>
</metadata>
</prolog>
<concept id="zide_overview" xml:lang="en-us">
<title>Overview</title>
<conbody>
<p>The following topics provide information about the zIDE development environment. They describe
the zIDE perspectives and views, the types of projects you can create in zIDE, how to set properties
for resources in zIDE, and the editors that you can use for COBOL, PL/I, Assembler, REXX, and C++
source files.</p>
<ul>
<li><xref href="../../com.ibm.etools.getstart.wsentdev.doc/topics/rzdcmn001.dita" type="reference"
/></li>
<li><xref href="../../com.ibm.wsentdev.doc/topics/czdcmn026.dita" type="concept" /></li>
<li><xref href="tzdpropgrp.dita" type="topic" /></li>
<li><xref format="html" href="../../com.ibm.etools.rdz.language.editors.doc/topics/czdcmn024.html" scope="peer" type="concept">Editing COBOL, PL/I, Assembler, and C++ files</xref></li>
</ul>
</conbody>
</concept>
<concept id="zide_gettingstarted" xml:lang="en-us">
<title>Getting started</title>
<conbody>
<p>The following topics provide instructions for completing some of the basic tasks you must do when
you develop applications in the zIDE.</p>
